==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grin
<hw>Grin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>grin</ets>.]</ety> <def>A snare; a gin.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like a bird that hasteth to his <qex>grin</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Remedy of Love.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Grin
<hw>Grin</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Grinned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Grinning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>grinnen</ets>,
<ets>grennen</ets>, AS. <ets>grennian</ets>, Sw. <ets>grina</ets>; akin
to D. <ets>grijnen</ets>, G. <ets>greinen</ets>, OHG. <ets>grinan</ets>,
Dan. <ets>grine</ets>. ⟦root⟧35. Cf. <er>Groan</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To show the teeth, as a dog; to snarl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To set the teeth together and open the lips, or to
open the mouth and withdraw the lips from the teeth, so as to show them,
as in laughter, scorn, or pain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pangs of death do make him <qex>grin</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Grin
<hw>Grin</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To express by grinning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Grinned</qex> horrible a ghastly smile.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Grin</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Grin
<hw>Grin</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of closing the teeth and
showing them, or of withdrawing the lips and showing the teeth; a hard,
forced, or sneering smile.</def> <rj><au>I.Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He showed twenty teeth at a <qex>grin</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grind</ent>⟦br⟧
